@Node "ins" "Checkstart.guide/ins"
@Toc "Main"

Manual Installation
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

First you have to copy the config file into the 's' drawer on your 'sys:' partion. Then just place
the main program anywhere you want, and run it from the startup-sequence.

Install program...
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

The install script copies the config file to SYS:c, and the main program to the Tools drawer in the 
SYS partion.

Remeber...
^^^^^^^^^^

Make sure to add the line between the LoadWB and Endcli commands, i.e.

....
C:LoadWB
run >NIL: sys:CheckStart
EndCLI >NIL:

You must remember to start Arexx further up in the script.


NOTE: If you have a boot-up picture, you must make sure that its screen has been closed
      BEFORE CheckStart starts!! This is because CheckStart opens on the further most screen!
@EndNode

