@Node "pro" "CheckStart.guide/pro"
@Toc "Main"

Editing the config file...
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
                                                   
Please note that the box made of '*'s should always make a perfect square! If it does not, you know
that there is a space in surplus. This must not happen, because then the program will not be able to
load/save the options!

Font sensitivity...
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

As I do not know how to make a program font sensitive, this program will force you to use the XEN.font,
this is not really a problem, as most people have this font, but I am unable to control the font used
for the title bar. This means that if you use a large font, e.g. if you have a graphics card running 
WB in a high resolution, it will 'eat' the space the gagets should have used! So try using a smaller
font, like the XEN.font.

Saving from the interface....
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

When having chosen a long path name to the script and saving it, you should be aware that changing
it to a shorter one will cause trouble. I.e. if the path was Work:scripts/start.script, you would
if you changed it to Work:start.script, get something like this in the config file: Work:start.scriptt.script. 
This is because that it just overrides the thing that was there before and does not delete anything
following it. You have to edit the config file to remove the unwanted bits.

Can't fileseek position...
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Remember to copy the 'CheckStart.config' file to your 's' directory!

@EndNode
